# ── Copy to `.env` for local development ─────────────────────────────────────
#   cp .env.example .env
# Vite reads only variables prefixed with VITE_.

# ── Blockchain RPC (comma-separated list allowed; first URL is used by Vite proxy) ──
VITE_RPC_URL=http://localhost:9933

# Optional: separate metrics endpoint
# VITE_METRICS_URL=http://localhost:9094

# ── API server (email/password sign-up, sign-in, magic link, SIWB) ────────────
# Local: run the Rust api-server on port 3030 (see ../../api-server/.env.example).
# Production (coinjecture.com): set to your public API origin, e.g. https://api.coinjecture.com
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3030

# ── Supabase (browser client — optional) ───────────────────────────────────
# Used where `src/lib/supabase.ts` is imported. Email auth from the UI goes through
# VITE_API_URL → api-server → Supabase Auth; you do not need these for signup unless
# other features use the client.
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxx.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...

# ── Production checklist (coinjecture.com) ───────────────────────────────────
# 1. Before `npm run build` / deploy.sh: copy `.env.production.example` → `.env.production`
#    and set VITE_API_URL to your public API (HTTPS).
# 2. api-server: SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET (and optional
#    SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY). Enable email in Supabase → Authentication → Providers / SMTP.
# 3. Supabase → URL Configuration: site URL + redirect URLs must include https://coinjecture.com
#    (and www if used). See supabase/config.toml for local mirror of redirect list.
# 4. api-server CORS: api-server/src/middleware/cors.rs (coinjecture.com + www already listed).
